Definition: The extent to which data in a bdqffdq:InformationElement are present and sufficiently comprehensive for use.
Comment: Definition from the Fitness for Use Framework: Data Quality Dimensions Document (Link needed to RDF document  - https://github.com/tdwg/bdq/wiki/TG2-Data-Quality-Dimension).

Definition: Where data in a bdqffdq:InformationElement conform to a format, syntax, data type, range, or standard.
Comment: Definition from the Fitness for Use Framework: Data Quality Dimensions Document (Link needed to RDF document  - https://github.com/tdwg/bdq/wiki/TG2-Data-Quality-Dimension).

Definition: Agreement among related bdqffdq:InformationElements that are present in the data. Note that missing bdqffdq:InformationElements do not make a test bdq:Inconsistent.
Comment: Definition from the Fitness for Use Framework: Data Quality Dimensions Document (Link needed to RDF document  - https://github.com/tdwg/bdq/wiki/TG2-Data-Quality-Dimension).

Definition: Where a bdqffdq:InformationElement does not contain sufficient information to satisfy the scope of the test.
Where bdqdim:Consistency is not satisfied due to inconsistent values between bdqffdq:InformationElements of a bdqffdq:SingleRecord.
Where bdqdim:Conformance is not satisfied due to bdqffdq:InformationElements containing non-standard values.
The likelihood of Darwin Core Term(s) having true or expected values.
Comment: Definition from the Fitness for Use Framework: Data Quality Dimensions Document (Link needed to RDF document  - https://github.com/tdwg/bdq/wiki/TG2-Data-Quality-Dimension).

Definition: A measure of the degree to which data values agree with and describe an identified source of truth (object, event or any abstract or real 'thing').
Comment: Definition from the Fitness for Use Framework: Data Quality Dimensions Document (Link needed to RDF document  - https://github.com/tdwg/bdq/wiki/TG2-Data-Quality-Dimension).

Definition: The extent to which the data have sufficiently detailed information. A measure of the granularity of the data, or the smallest measurable increment.
Comment: Definition from the Fitness for Use Framework: Data Quality Dimensions Document (Link needed to RDF document  - https://github.com/tdwg/bdq/wiki/TG2-Data-Quality-Dimension).

Definition: Where bdqdim:Likeliness is not satisfied due to the bdqffdq:InformationElements containing a value that is not likely to occur (for example where the geographic coordinates are "0", "0").
Comment: Needs a bdq:Response.qualifier (_q.v._) response for the uncertainty.

Definition: Where bdqdim:Conformance is not satisfied due to bdqffdq:InformationElements not being unambiguously resolvable by a bdq:sourceAuthority.
